snippet.title: Visual Blocks:  Ridiculously rapid ML/AI prototyping and deployment to production
snippet.description:
Visual Blocks from Google is an open source graphical programming framework for rapid prototyping and experimentation of production ideas powered by machine learning. It enables developers and decision-makers alike to work together to solve problems through powerful reusable building blocks, iterate, and then deploy with ease for all to try. You can build an end to end ML pipeline to share with your team in minutes! 

In this video learn how to use Visual Blocks through real-world examples so you can adapt this knowledge to your own products and services. From creating your own social media worthy augmented reality effects on a live webcam feed, to running LLMs and generative models in a Colab powered by this visual framework to experiment chaining inputs, other models, and outputs together in powerful ways, the options are almost limitless as to what you can achieve using Visual Blocks.

We would love to hear your feedback over on the Visual Blocks Website: https://goo.gle/VisualBlocksML for feature requests and more!

Resources to use in this tutorial:
Portrait image → https://goo.gle/3OcNqNR
Hearts overlay → https://goo.gle/3LMDJCF
Sunset background → https://goo.gle/3VS5D4P

snippet.title: Harnessing the power of generative AI to deliver next-gen search experiences
snippet.description:
With the rise of Large Language Models, search engines are rapidly evolving with the "semantic search" capability. Not only do they find information with keyword matching, they deeply understand the meaning and intent of user queries from searching across texts and images to realize the AI-driven user experience (AI-UX) that is becoming the new standard. Tune into this session to explore the out-of-the-box dev tools from Enterprise Search that answers user questions like never before.

snippet.title: Gaming with muscular dystrophy | Project GameFace featuring Lance Carr | Google
snippet.description:
Lance Carr - a Colorado gamer with a rare form of muscular dystrophy - was at home playing video games one afternoon when a fire turned his life upside down. 

This year at I/O, we’re celebrating Lance’s resilient return to gaming. Over the last year, Lance collaborated with a team of Googlers to co-create a new technology that uses MediaPipe and Tensor Flow Lite to turn facial gestures into mouse movements. The resulting solution is now open-sourced and available for everyone to game and create with. 

For a quick recap of Google I/O, check out this video: https://youtu.be/QpBTM0GO6xI

snippet.title: Developers guide to BigQuery export for Google Analytics 4
snippet.description:
With Google Analytics 4 (GA4), anyone can set up export of granular measurement data to BigQuery.

In this session, you will learn how to use the BigQuery export for solving business problems, doing complex reporting, implementing advanced use cases with ML models, and creating custom audiences by joining with first-party data. You can use this framework for detailed or large-scale data analysis. We will also share some best practices to get you started.
